    Page: 132
    Verse: 20
Tags:
  - Envy
---
Our knowledge of what the richer than ourselves possess, and the poor do
not, has never been more widespread. Therefore, envy, which is wanting what
others have, and jealousy, which is not wanting others to have what one
has, have never been more widespread.
